Name: QUALIFIER
Explanation: A UNIQUE CODE WHICH CAVEATS A MESSAGE STATUS.

Name: ELEVATION QUALIFIER
Explanation: THE CRITERIA USED TO DETERMINE THE STARTING POINT OF THE ELEVATION MEASUREMENT.

Name: ALPHA INDEX QUALIFIER
Explanation: A QUALIFIER OF THE INDEX OF SUNSPOT ACTIVITY.

Name: TACAN CHANNEL MODE QUALIFIER
Explanation: A SPECIFIC LETTER QUALIFIER IDENTIFYING ONE OF THE TWO POSSIBLE MODES OF A TACAN RADIO CHANNELIZED EMISSION, EITHER X OR Y.

Name: ABOVE MEAN SEA LEVEL DATA QUALIFIER
Explanation: ABOVE MEAN SEA LEVEL (AMSL) DATA QUALIFIER

Name: ROE DPC STATUS CODE
Explanation: STATUS OF THE RULES OF ENGAGEMENT THAT MAY BE IMPLEMENTED AT THE DPC LEVEL.

Name: ROE MNC STATUS CODE
Explanation: STATUS OF THE RULES OF ENGAGEMENT THAT MAY BE IMPLEMENTED AT THE MNC LEVEL.

Name: SEARCH ATTACK UNIT OR SURFACE ACTION GROUP QUALIFIER
PASSAGE USABILITY
Explanation: TO DESCRIBE WHETHER A PASSAGE IS PASSABLE OR NOT.

Name: CONNECTED SENSORS QUALIFIER
Explanation: THE DIFFERENT TYPE OF SENSORS CONNECTED TO A COMMAND AND CONTROL UNIT.

Name: OPERATION QUALIFIER
Explanation: A QUALIFIER USED TO SUB-CATEGORISE A TYPE OF OPERATION.

Name: OPDEF QUALIFIER
Explanation: PROVIDES THE OPDEF QUALIFIER IF THIS IS NOT THE INITIAL SIGNAL FOR AN OPDEF.
